{"title":"Chromag Updated the Rootdown 29er Hardtail","link":"https://theradavist.com/update-chromag-rootdown-29er-hardtail/","date":1718756367000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1338\" height=\"893\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_01.jpg?fit=1200,893&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_01.jpg?w=1338&amp;quality=75 1338w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_01.jpg?resize=1200,801&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_01.jpg?resize=768,513&amp;quality=75 768w\" /></p>\n<p><em><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/?s=Chromag\" target=\"_blank\">Chromag</a> is synonymous with hardtails. Trail hardtails. And the 160 mm travel <a href=\"https://us.chromagbikes.com/products/rootdown-2024?shpxid=c0a5267c-367a-44f6-9828-400274e36968&amp;variant=41825778499716\" target=\"_blank\">Rootdown</a> ($801 frame, $3,912 complete) is now in its sixth iteration. The updates this round are chassis details and new build specs so let’s check it out… </em><span></span></p>\n<p><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_03.jpeg?fit=1200,1067&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_03.jpeg?w=1600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_03.jpeg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_03.jpeg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_03.jpeg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>The new Rootdown continues a story that has been evolving since Chromag started making hardtail frames over twenty years ago. These Taiwan-made frames use 4130 chromoly steel tubing, designed to be strong and offer a smooth ride quality. Chromoly is much stronger than traditional 1020 steel, and it has a higher strength-to-weight ratio and high tensile strength, which means the engineers can use less material and achieve a product that can withstand the abuse that riders love to throw at it.</p>\n<p><img width=\"1068\" height=\"1600\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_06.jpeg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_06.jpeg?w=1068&amp;quality=75 1068w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_06.jpeg?resize=768,1151&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_06.jpeg?resize=1025,1536&amp;quality=75 1025w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2091\" height=\"1394\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_05.jpeg?fit=1200,1394&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_05.jpeg?w=2091&amp;quality=75 2091w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_05.jpeg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_05.jpeg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_05.jpeg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_05.jpeg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_05.jpeg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"866\" height=\"1298\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_04.jpeg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_04.jpeg?w=866&amp;quality=75 866w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_04.jpeg?resize=768,1151&amp;quality=75 768w\" /></p>\n<p>The Series VI carries forward the tried and tested geometry the Rootdown is known for with all sizing specs remaining consistent to the previous version. New for 2024 are updates to tubing, finishes, the machined junctions, and interfaces: a refinement of the chassis and construction.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2854\" height=\"1348\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_Geo.jpg?fit=1200,1348&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_Geo.jpg?w=2854&amp;quality=75 2854w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_Geo.jpg?resize=1200,567&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_Geo.jpg?resize=2000,945&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_Geo.jpg?resize=768,363&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_Geo.jpg?resize=1536,725&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Chromag_Rootdown_Geo.jpg?resize=2048,967&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>This latest model has been updated with post-mount brake tabs, a UDH hanger, threaded BB, and E.D. tube coating to extend the lifespan of the frame. E.D. (Electrophoretic Deposition) coating is the process of applying a thin layer of coating to all surfaces of a part, both inside and out.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1219\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Rootdown-frame-black.jpg?fit=1200,1219&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Rootdown-frame-black.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Rootdown-frame-black.jpg?resize=1200,731&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Rootdown-frame-black.jpg?resize=768,468&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/Rootdown-frame-black.jpg?resize=1536,936&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /> <img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1240\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/chromag-rootdown-frame-chestnut.jpg?fit=1200,1240&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/chromag-rootdown-frame-chestnut.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/chromag-rootdown-frame-chestnut.jpg?resize=1200,744&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/chromag-rootdown-frame-chestnut.jpg?resize=768,476&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/chromag-rootdown-frame-chestnut.jpg?resize=1536,952&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Wheel Size // 29″ or 27+</li>\n<li>Recommended Fork Travel // 160mm (±10mm)</li>\n<li>Colors: Chestnut brown and black gradient</li>\n<li>Material // 4130 Chromoly Steel</li>\n<li>Frame Weight (M/L) // 7.13lbs</li>\n<li>Hub Spacing // Boost 148mm (Axle Included)</li>\n<li>Headset // 44-56 Semi Integrated</li>\n<li>Seat Clamp Size // 35mm</li>\n<li>Seat Post Size // 31.6mm</li>\n<li>BB // BSA 73mm Threaded</li>\n<li>Hanger // UDH (Included)</li>\n<li>Brake Mount // 180mm Post</li>\n<li>Frame Origin // Taiwan</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1345\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/chromag-rootdown-complete-chestn.jpg?fit=1200,1345&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/chromag-rootdown-complete-chestn.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/chromag-rootdown-complete-chestn.jpg?resize=1200,807&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/chromag-rootdown-complete-chestn.jpg?resize=768,516&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/06/chromag-rootdown-complete-chestn.jpg?resize=1536,1033&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong>G2 Build</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fork // Rock Shox Lyrik Select 160mm Boost 110x15mm</li>\n<li>Stem // Chromag HiFi BSX 40mm</li>\n<li>Bar// Chromag OSX 25mm Rise, 800mm</li>\n<li>Headset // Cane Creek Forty ZS</li>\n<li>Crank // SRAM GX 170mm</li>\n<li>Brakes // SRAM G2 RSC</li>\n<li>Rotors // SRAM 180mm</li>\n<li>Shifter // SRAM GX Eagle</li>\n<li>Cassette // SRAM GX Eagle 10-52t</li>\n<li>Derailleur // SRAM GX Eagle</li>\n<li>Rims // Chromag 29″ Phase30</li>\n<li>Hubs // Chromag R4</li>\n<li>Tires // Maxxis Minion DHF/DHR</li>\n<li>Seatpost // RockShox Reverb<br />\n(125mm – S) (150mm – M) (175mm – M/L) (200mm – L, XL)</li>\n<li>Saddle // Chromag Trailmaster DT</li>\n<li>Grips // Chromag Format</li>\n<li>Chain // SRAM GX Eagle</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Check out more at <a href=\"https://us.chromagbikes.com/products/rootdown-2024?shpxid=c0a5267c-367a-44f6-9828-400274e36968&amp;variant=41825778499716\" target=\"_blank\">Chromag</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/update-chromag-rootdown-29er-hardtail/\">Chromag Updated the Rootdown 29er Hardtail</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"50af16f39ab6c12265891aa37f68333e0ba6729ca5fd031c7db1a79c103d5731","category":"Cycling"}